This project is set up mostly according to http://www.jeffknupp.com/blog/2013/12/18/starting-a-django-16-project-the-right-way/

To get a dev environment set up the first time:
1. Install Python and pip
2. pip install virtualenv
3. In the balningau directory:
   a. virtualenv .
   b. source bin/activate
   c. pip install -r requirements.txt
   d. ./manage.py syncdb
   e. ./manage.py migrate

And thereafter:
1. In the balningau directory:
   a. source bin/activate
   b. ./manage.py runserver

